"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly applies the fit_transform method of RobustScaler to both the training and test sets separately. This can lead to data leakage and improper scaling, as the test set should be transformed using the parameters learned from the training set. Instead, fit_transform should be called on the training set, and transform should be called on the test set.\", \"patch\": \"11c11\\n< X_test_scaled = rb_scaler.fit_transform(X_test)\\n---\\n> X_test_scaled = rb_scaler.transform(X_test)\"}"